Nike said Monday that it will no longer be using kangaroo leather in its products by the end of the year, an announcement that comes just weeks after Puma said it would stop using the material in soccer boots in 2023.

Kangaroo leather—often marketed to the public as ‘k-leather’—has been a fixture of soccer cleats for years. ESPN identified more than 70 types of cleats on Soccer.com containing kangaroo leather, offered not only by Puma and Nike, but also brands like Adidas, New Balance, and Mizuno.

Though there is no federal law in the U.S. restricting kangaroo leather, a bipartisan bill was introduced in the House in 2021 to ‘prohibit and criminalize the import, transport, and sale of all kangaroo products in the United States for commercial purposes,’ per ESPN.

A similar bill was introduced in the Oregon state legislature earlier this year. Nike is based in Oregon and is one of the state’s most influential companies.

The kangaroo leather industry has historically been worth hundreds of millions to Australia’s economy. However, it has taken a hit in recent years as sports companies and other fashion brands like H&M, Prada, and Versace have also publicly pledged to avoid using the material.

Slide 1 - Knee extension: If you suffer a knee injury or have just undergone knee surgery, your terminal knee extension will likely be limited. This means that you will not be able to lock your knee in place. The goal of knee extension exercises in this scenario is to essentially help you to slowly improve, or extend the end range of motion in your knees.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 2 - Knee mobility: The knee is usually trained in sagittal plane, but rarely if ever in a transverse plane. Start training your knee in all degrees 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 3 - Knee flexion/quad stretch: The key to improve knee flexion after surgery is gently pushing into that uncomfortable range and trying to progressively increase the amount of time you spend there with each successive day. In this drill I am using a prone band quad stretch PNF of 5s:5s. Proprioceptive Neuromuscular Facilitation (PNF) is a more advanced form of flexibility training. PNF involves both stretching and contracting (activation) of the muscle group being targeted in order to achieve maximum static flexibility.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Slide 4 - Isometrics: Isometric exercise is the technique of engaging your muscles without movement. Isometrics strengthens your connective tissues. Tendons and ligaments are the parts of your body that hold everything together. The stronger your connective tissue is, the stronger you will be. In addition, the stronger your tendons and ligaments are the less likely you are to be injured.

⁠
A predominately suede construction takes over while overlays are dyed in a deep black. Cream underlays and touches of “Coconut Milk” can also be found throughout the relatively neutral shoe. No release details have surfaced yet but stay tuned in the meantime.⁠

@hypebeastkicks: @cactusplantfleamarket and @nike are reuniting for another Dunk Low collaboration. The upcoming pair features two-tone suede uppers accented by a triangular pattern. Additional detailing sees oversized Swooshes in white, embroidered mini swooshes, puffy tongues, mismatched sockliners and laces, yin yang motifs, and special insoles. Extending green mudguards and matching sole units round out the design of the pair. You can expect these to drop later this year. ⁠

The Lionesses will now wear dark shorts at this summer's World Cup, the FA has revealed - after discussions between the association, the players and kit supplier, Nike.

Following feedback from the England players on the impracticalities of having to play in the all-white kit whilst being on their period, their home and away kits will now feature blue shorts. 

In addition to the darker colourway, the shorts feature a 'leak protection' liner, so players can focus on their performance, not waste energy thinking about leaking while playing on their period.

'We know for the first 45 minutes [of a match] they can't leave the pitch and for the first nine minutes on average they're thinking about the potential of leaking [if they're on their period], or if they're about to or if they already are,' Charlotte Harris, senior women's designer at Nike Global Apparel Design, told The Telegraph.

'That's a huge chunk of time...So we knew this was something we needed to innovate against to be able to deliver for our female athletes, so we can remove that distraction and they can stay focused.'

Head to the link in bio for more on this huge step for women in sport 🙌👏

Description:
Nike continues its crusade, filing a lawsuit against Bape alleging they have copied Nike sneaker designs.⁠
⁠
Nike is suing Bape, accusing the Japanese brand of copying Air Force 1, Air Jordan, and Dunk designs. ⁠
⁠
Describing the copies as "near verbatim" Nike said BAPE's U.S. sales of the shoes were "sporadic" until 2021, when it "drastically increased the volume and scope of its infringement."⁠
⁠
"BAPE's copying is and always has been unacceptable to Nike, and because BAPE's infringements have recently grown to become a significant danger to Nike's rights, Nike must act now," the lawsuit said.⁠
⁠
Nike asked the court to order BAPE to stop selling the shoes and requested an unspecified amount of money damages.⁠
⁠
The case is Nike Inc v. USAPE LLC, U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York, No. 1:23-cv-00660.⁠
⁠
📷: Bape

Social media users blasted woke Nike @nike for “mocking Jesus” after the company posted a tribute to LeBron James @kingjames containing religious language.

On Tuesday, Nike made a tribute video to their biggest active pitchman, LeBron James, after he passed Kareem Abdul-Jabbar as the NBA’s all-time leading scorer. However, the black-and-white video contained music and language of a decidedly religious nature and angered many of those who viewed it online.

“Do we have anyone in the building today willing to testify? Talk to me now; he’s done so much already,” the voice in the video says. We’ve witnessed him do so much already. We’ve heard about the things this man can do already. And we just can’t help but celebrate him. Haters, go ahead and recognize, that when you speak on his name, you’re gonna go higher, higher, higher. So excuse me while I cut a step, ‘cause I can’t help but to honor him. I can’t help but to lift him up. I got one last question for ya. Can I get a witness? Can I get a witness? I said can I get a witness?” The “Witness” language is not new. During the early stages of James’ career, Nike launched a promotional campaign dubbed WITNESS. However, that campaign had more to do with signage and fewer obvious religious connotations than a preacher screaming into a microphone.

The heavy doses of religion and allusions to Jesus in a tribute video to a basketball player did not go unnoticed by fans on Instagram.

Description:
@hypebeastkicks: @nike has revealed that its SNKRS release platform receives nearly 12 billion bot entries per month.⁠
⁠
The footwear giant unveiled the news during a recent presentation at the S23NYC office, with SNKRS General Manager and Vice President Lucy Rouse also sharing that almost half of the entries — which is tallied at millions — for the recent releases of the @travisscott x Air Jordan 1 Low OG “Olive” and the Air Jordan 1 “Lost And Found” were bots. Meanwhile, for La Flame's “Reverse Mocha,” the platform received almost 3.8 million entries and almost 1.9 million of those were bots.⁠
⁠
Rouse reassured, however, that the Swoosh's bot removal success rate is as high as 98%; its later releases have included a “Verifying submissions…” page after the payment procedure, which is part of the company’s effort to clear out any bot submissions. Nike has also introduced the likes of SNKRS Pass, SNKRS Draw, SNKRS Flow, SNKRS Scratcher, and SNKRS Cam in the past to ensure that the entries are legitimate.⁠
⁠
Photo: Eddie Lee/Hypebeast

Blogged by: @cabbagepatchgrl⁠

#FootLocker is expected to shut down over 400 store locations by 2026.⁠
⁠
Generally, stores that are underperforming and located in malls will be affected.  The retail giant says it will open new formats and transform its real estate footprint.⁠
⁠
Foot Locker also revealed their new “Lace Up” plan, which a new strategic plan will manage.  This involves enhancing the customer’s online purchasing experience, boosting its selection of sneakers, differentiating its banner stores, and resetting the company’s reward program.⁠

Additionally, Footlocker will announce a new #Nike partnership this holiday season.⁠
⁠
“Nike is our largest brand partner and the leader in the industry,” #MaryDillon, Foot Locker Inc.’s CEO, said. “My team and I have spent much time with Nike revitalizing our partnership.”

🌩️🌩️Air Jordan IV “Thunder” comparison: 2006 🆚 2012 🆚 2023

It’s crazy to imagine that a shoe that was originally super rare in 2006 has now retro’d twice as a GR. On August 23, 2006, the “Thunder 4’s” first released as an online exclusive to jumpman23.com members for $500. Included with the shoes was a matching laser print inspired jacket and retro card. The package was limited to only 500 pairs making it one of the most rare Air Jordan to release to the public. 

The next version released on December 22, 2012 for $160. Comes in an OG style box and a thick plastic hangtag. No jacket this time but definitely more widely available. The overall look and shape improved a tiny bit but this was still before the Brand’s “remastering phase”. The 2012’s have a slightly brighter yellow and the toe stars are a little more prominent. One small detail I noticed is the lace locks by the toe do not have the extra flared piece like the 06/23’s. This release was a bit controversial since many fans were upset to see such a limited sneaker become widely available. 

The most recent version released last Saturday (May 13, 2023) for $210. These utilize the improved shape that Jordan Brand has implemented on their recent 4’s. They are also a higher cut than the previous models. The yellow has a slightly darker hue which is really only noticeable when all 3 are lined up. The “Air Jordan” tag behind the tongue has been changed to black. The netting runs more parallel to the wing as it should, and the stars on the toe are even more prominent. 

If I take the limited availability out of the equation, I’ll give the 2023 pair the win. Shape wise, it’s my favorite of the three. While the jacket is a nice inclusion, the overall look of the 2006 is just inferior. The yellow color hues don’t sway me much.

Upcoming #eBay x #Nike SB Dunk Low ‘Sandy Bodecker’ ‼️🔥 via @prvt.selection 

The eBay x Nike SB Dunk Low is truly a unique shoe that was available via an eBay auction in 2003. For 2022, the pair will return close to its original form but will have a new addition that pays tribute to the original pair. 

In 2003, Nike produced a single pair of the eBay x Nike SB Dunk Low. The auction winner would be able to pick their size, which ended at $26,000. For years, it wasn’t known who the winner was other than rumors of it being a Nike employee. What raised more suspicion was the winner was located in Beaverton, Oregon. 

It turns out the auction’s winner was none other than Sandy Bodecker. For years, many thought there were three pairs in existence. However, Sandy cleared this up before his passing on his Instagram, stating there are only two pairs made. The other pair is cut up and in Nike SBs vault.

Are y’all excited for these ⁉️🤔 Let us know your thoughts in the comments below👇

@hypebeaststyle: Michael Jordan's notorious 1992 Summer Olympics "Dream Team" Reebok Jacket is headed for auction.⁠
⁠
The NBA legend donned the jacket when he accepted his gold medal for his 1992 victory in Barcelona. He draped an American flag over the right side of the jacket during the ceremony to cover up the Reebok logo. Despite being contractually obligated to be wearing the Reebok apparel at the games, Jordan wanted to ensure that his loyalty was with Nike.⁠
⁠
Those looking to own a piece of American basketball history can bid for the jacket between June 20 to 28 at @sothebys Dream Team sale.⁠
Photo: Getty Images/Sotheby's⁠
⁠

@hypebeaststyle: @cactusplantfleamarket and @nike are back for a new apparel collection, continuing the use of big logos, bold colors, boisterous details, baggy cuts, and bootleg inspiration. The five-piece range includes a jacket, a quarter-zip fleece, a crewneck sweatshirt, a polo shirt, pants, and, in a first for the partnership, a large blanket. ⁠
⁠
The fisherman-inspired jacket leads the offering, as it’s loaded with pouches and pockets. while also featuring a floatie-inspired red Swoosh on its zipper and a water-repellent finish. Other highlights include the large Dri-FIT sock that’s stitched on the front of the crewneck and pulls double duty as a pocket, the all-over bootleg logo print on the quarter-zip fleece, and the rich grass-inspired texture on the blanket.⁠
⁠
Expect all the pieces to hit Nike SNKRS on October 27.⁠

⁠
The silhouette's signature features include exaggerated tailpipe Swooshes inspired by the blast pipes of Japanese Bosozoku bikes and semi-detached heel tab panels made to resemble fenders. Furthermore, large AMBUSH lettering decorates the heel counter and additional motifs are found on the metallic lace dubrae, co-branded tongue tab, and insoles. Rounding out the look are classic AF1 sole units featuring subtle branding on the bottoms.⁠
⁠
Expect the pairs to hit Nike and select retailers on February 28 for $190 USD.⁠

Description:
OG Ma, the 50-year-old Chinese Mother of Streetwear

If you’re a fan of streetwear, it could mean you’re also a fan or familiar with OG Ma (original gangster mother). Hypebeasts only dream of having her steezy ‘fits and exceptional knowledge for all-things streetwear.

OG Ma, born Lam Xie, moved with her two sons from Shenzhen, China to New York City in 1992. In the city that never sleeps, Ma began her grind while attending university to complete her business degree. 

While Ma was in her studies, Peter, one of her son’s became obsessed with the NYC street style scene. He began collecting brands like #Supreme and #BAPE, and in 2006 decided to open up a small shop in the basement of a Chinatown mall called Unique Hype. 

Peter’s business was steady but nothing extreme, that was until he asked his mother to jump on board as the day-to-day manager. OG Ma immediately quit her babysitting job, took the job offer & went all in. 

Unique Hype was ahead of its time. The store launched when collecting streetwear items was considered a new idea loved by a small niche of streetwear enthusiasts.

Unique Hype started off small, but word of mouth started travelling around, and in 2014, the shop had its first celebrity visitor, Wiz Khalifa. When he entered he saw OG Ma sitting behind the counter. The rapper enjoyed his experience, purchased clothes, and took a picture with Ma for the Unique Hype’s IG page. 

Later that year, Travis Scott stopped in, and a few months later, Kylie Jenner arrived with a bouquet of roses to gift OG Ma with – the legend she had heard plenty about. 

Why do they call her OG Ma? She told the Cut, “Because, they tell me, I know everything: OG Nike SB, OG Supreme, Kaws, KidRobot — OG everything.” And it’s true, this Chinese woman in her 50s knows just about everything to do with the history of sneakers, and rare clothing items. 

Perhaps Unique Hype exploded in popularity for its rare streetwear and hype clothing items, but OG Ma knew how to run a business, and quickly became the face of the shop. Visitors now stop to shop for rare hype-wear and to experience quality time with the mother of streetwear.

That’s Baller: Rare 1999 Wu-Tang x Nike Dunks Selling for $50,000⁠

Blogged by: @Thefineauthor

One pair of the extremely rare #WuTang x #NikeDunks High is being sold exclusively on JustinReed.com, but they’re going to cost you.⁠
⁠
The rare sneaker is only one of 36 pairs produced as part of the 1999 Nike “Be True” collection. The black and yellow high-top sneaker sports the signature Wu-Tang logo on the side of the footwear. Known as a rare gem amongst sneaker enthusiasts, Wu-Tang made sure their emblem stood out, placing the black graphic against the yellow port of the shoe. The patent leather upper within itself is a rarity considering that the Dunks of today do not utilize this material often in newer shoes.⁠
⁠
Available in a size nine, this pair of Dunks have landed at JustinReed.com, the luxury consignment shop and curator that offers some of the rarest pieces in fashion, art, and furniture. The Dunks are listed as gently worn and in excellent condition on the website.⁠
⁠
The single pair of sneakers are available for purchase now, though they will not be acquired by just anyone...to read the rest log on to BallerAlert.com (clickable link on profile)⁠
